1
00:00:01,369 --> 00:00:03,137
- APRIL!

2
00:00:03,171 --> 00:00:04,272
LISTEN, I WAS TRYING TO BUY

3
00:00:04,305 --> 00:00:06,174
THIS HAND-CRAFTED
MAHOGANY WOOD MODEL

4
00:00:06,207 --> 00:00:09,077
OF A B-25 MITCHELL
PANCHITO AIRCRAFT.

5
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:11,279
- AW, FOR ME?
- DON'T SASS ME.

6
00:00:11,312 --> 00:00:13,514
AND I WENT TO THIS WEBSITE,
AND THIS AD POPPED UP

7
00:00:13,547 --> 00:00:15,516
THAT SAID "HEY, RON SWANSON!

8
00:00:15,549 --> 00:00:17,551
CHECK OUT THIS GREAT OFFER."

9
00:00:17,585 --> 00:00:19,487
- WHAT'S YOUR QUESTION?

10
00:00:19,520 --> 00:00:21,522
- MY QUESTION IS,
WHAT THE HELL?

11
00:00:21,555 --> 00:00:23,424
- LIKE, HOW DID THEY KNOW
WHO YOU ARE?

12
00:00:23,457 --> 00:00:25,659
- YEAH.
- OKAY.

13
00:00:25,693 --> 00:00:28,262
UM, THERE ARE THESE THINGS
CALLED COOKIES,

14
00:00:28,296 --> 00:00:30,498
WHERE, LIKE, IF YOU GO TO A SITE
AND BUY SOMETHING,

15
00:00:30,531 --> 00:00:32,733
IT'LL REMEMBER YOU
AND THEN CREATE ADS

16
00:00:32,766 --> 00:00:34,302
FOR OTHER STUFF
YOU MIGHT WANT TO BUY.

17
00:00:34,335 --> 00:00:37,338
- SO IT LEARNS INFORMATION?
ABOUT ME?

18
00:00:37,371 --> 00:00:39,507
THAT SEEMS LIKE AN INVASION
OF PRIVACY.

19
00:00:39,540 --> 00:00:41,209
- DUDE, IF YOU THINK
THAT'S BAD,

20
00:00:41,242 --> 00:00:44,245
GO TO GOOGLE EARTH
AND TYPE IN YOUR ADDRESS.

21
00:00:53,421 --> 00:00:56,390
[triumphant music]

22
00:00:56,424 --> 00:01:04,665
*

23
00:01:18,379 --> 00:01:20,881
- I AM, OF COURSE, SHOCKED...

24
00:01:20,914 --> 00:01:24,418
AND NOT JUST BECAUSE BEN
USUALLY PREFERS TALL BRUNETTES.

25
00:01:24,452 --> 00:01:25,519
- WE'RE VERY SORRY

26
00:01:25,553 --> 00:01:28,622
FOR THE POSITION
THIS PUTS YOU IN.

27
00:01:28,656 --> 00:01:29,890
- WHAT'S HAPPENING?

28
00:01:29,923 --> 00:01:31,425
ARE YOU HUGGING ME,
OR ARE WE FIGHTING?

29
00:01:31,459 --> 00:01:32,426
ARE YOU HUGGING OR FIGHTING?
LET ME KNOW.

30
00:01:32,460 --> 00:01:34,462
- NEITHER OF THOSE THINGS.

31
00:01:34,495 --> 00:01:36,264
I LOVE BOTH OF YOU.

32
00:01:36,297 --> 00:01:38,499
YOU ARE EXEMPLARY
GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES.

33
00:01:38,532 --> 00:01:41,402
- "EXEMPLARY"? THAT'S THE WORD
WE WERE THINKING OF.

34
00:01:41,435 --> 00:01:43,471
- WELL, IT'S TRUE.
- ISN'T IT?

35
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,273
- WHICH MAKES WHAT
I'M ABOUT TO SAY EVEN SADDER.

36
00:01:45,306 --> 00:01:46,707
- THEN DON'T SAY IT.

37
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:48,276
- I'M LAUNCHING
A FULL INVESTIGATION

38
00:01:48,309 --> 00:01:49,810
INTO THE EXTENT
OF YOUR WRONGDOING.

39
00:01:49,843 --> 00:01:52,446
PLEASE REPORT MONDAY FIRST THING
TO THE COUNCIL CHAMBERS

40
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,883
FOR YOUR ETHICS TRIAL
AND SUBSEQUENT PUNISHMENT.

41
00:01:59,253 --> 00:02:01,455
- I TOLD YOU
WE'D FEEL BETTER.

42
00:02:03,591 --> 00:02:04,858
[door opens]
HEY.

43
00:02:04,892 --> 00:02:06,494
IT'S 6:30 IN THE MORNING.

44
00:02:06,527 --> 00:02:09,330
YOUR HEARING DOESN'T START
FOR ANOTHER TWO HOURS.

45
00:02:09,363 --> 00:02:10,598
- WELL, I WANTED
TO GET HERE EARLY,

46
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:12,200
YOU KNOW,
GET A FEEL OF THE ROOM.

47
00:02:12,233 --> 00:02:14,468
- SO YOU GOT HERE--
- 3:00 A.M.

48
00:02:14,502 --> 00:02:15,569
I COULDN'T SLEEP ANYWAY.

49
00:02:15,603 --> 00:02:18,406
- WELL, I WANTED TO SNEAK IN
BEFORE YOU GOT HERE--

50
00:02:18,439 --> 00:02:21,375
AN ABSURD PIPE DREAM
I NOW REALIZE WAS IMPOSSIBLE.

51
00:02:21,409 --> 00:02:22,810
- IS THAT A PRESENT FOR ME?

52
00:02:22,843 --> 00:02:24,545
- YEAH.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

53
00:02:24,578 --> 00:02:26,814
- [gasps]
LI'L SEBASTIAN.

54
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:28,516
- YEAH, I HAD HIM MADE FOR YOU
AT THE TOY STORE.

55
00:02:28,549 --> 00:02:31,385
- AW, THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR MAKING MY LIFE SO WONDERFUL.

56
00:02:31,419 --> 00:02:33,254
- YOU'RE WELCOME.
- I WAS TALKING TO HIM.

57
00:02:33,287 --> 00:02:34,688
- OF COURSE.
- BUT ALSO TO YOU.

58
00:02:34,722 --> 00:02:36,257
- THANKS.

59
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:37,525
- I WISH WE COULD GO
THROUGH THIS TOGETHER.

60
00:02:37,558 --> 00:02:38,859
- LOOK, IT'S GOING TO BE OKAY.

61
00:02:38,892 --> 00:02:40,694
YOU'RE JUST GONNA GET
A SLAP ON THE WRIST,

62
00:02:40,728 --> 00:02:42,430
MAYBE A BRIEF SUSPENSION.

63
00:02:42,463 --> 00:02:43,597
- THAT'S NOT OKAY.

64
00:02:43,631 --> 00:02:45,266
THAT'S GONNA GO
ON MY PERMANENT RECORD.

65
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:47,235
I'M NOT THE KIND OF PERSON
THAT HAS A PERMANENT RECORD.

66
00:02:47,268 --> 00:02:50,238
FOR ME, A SLAP ON THE WRIST
IS LIKE A KICK TO THE NUTS.

67
00:02:50,271 --> 00:02:51,939
- I KNOW IT IS.

68
00:02:51,972 --> 00:02:53,507
- WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO YOU?

69
00:02:53,541 --> 00:02:56,310
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.

70
00:02:56,344 --> 00:02:57,845
WELL, LOOK, I'LL BE OUTSIDE
ALL DAY,

71
00:02:57,878 --> 00:02:59,880
RIGHT ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THAT WALL.

72
00:02:59,913 --> 00:03:03,417
SO, IF YOU MISS ME,
YOU JUST LOOK AT THIS...

73
00:03:03,451 --> 00:03:05,319
WRINKLED, HIDEOUS MONSTER

74
00:03:05,353 --> 00:03:07,388
AND YOU'LL KNOW
I'M SITTING THERE

75
00:03:07,421 --> 00:03:09,990
ROOTING FOR YOU, OKAY?
- OKAY.

76
00:03:10,023 --> 00:03:11,359
- ALL RIGHT.

77
00:03:11,392 --> 00:03:12,793
- GO.
- OKAY.

78
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:15,396
- MARCUS EVERETT LANGLEY
WAS PAWNEE'S GREATEST LAWYER

79
00:03:15,429 --> 00:03:16,864
AT THE TURN OF THE CENTURY.

80
00:03:16,897 --> 00:03:19,400
HIS NICKNAME
WAS "OLD STONE FACE"

81
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:20,734
BECAUSE OF HIS STEELY DEMEANOR

82
00:03:20,768 --> 00:03:22,870
AND BECAUSE HE GOT IN
AN ACCIDENT AT THE ROCK QUARRY

83
00:03:22,903 --> 00:03:25,506
AND DYNAMITE BLEW UP HIS FACE.

84
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:27,541
- LESLIE KNOPE!
GOOD MORNING!

85
00:03:27,575 --> 00:03:30,010
IT IS SNOWING OUTSIDE.
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

86
00:03:30,043 --> 00:03:31,412
- YOU SEEM LIKE
YOU'RE IN A GOOD MOOD.

87
00:03:31,445 --> 00:03:33,381
- ACTUALLY,
I'M QUITE MISERABLE.

88
00:03:33,414 --> 00:03:35,383
I ADMIRE AND RESPECT YOU,

89
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:37,451
AND DRAGGING YOU
THROUGH AN ETHICS TRIAL

90
00:03:37,485 --> 00:03:38,786
IS FILLING ME WITH SADNESS.

91
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:42,356
I HAVE NEVER FELT SO LOW.

92
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:44,325
- WELL, YOU'RE RADIATING
PURE JOY.

93
00:03:44,358 --> 00:03:46,560
- I WENT TO MY HERBALIST
AND GOT TWO B-12 SHOTS.

94
00:03:46,594 --> 00:03:49,663
AND THEN I ATE AN UNREASONABLE
AMOUNT OF ST. JOHN'S WORT,

95
00:03:49,697 --> 00:03:51,899
AND MY HERBALIST TOOK
THIS WEIRD BEE POLLEN PASTE

96
00:03:51,932 --> 00:03:53,434
RUBBED IT AROUND MY GUMS.

97
00:03:53,467 --> 00:03:55,469
AND NOW MY MOUTH FEELS
LIKE A SPACESHIP.

98
00:03:55,503 --> 00:03:57,471
THIS IS STRESSFUL.

99
00:04:05,413 --> 00:04:06,714
OH, GOD.

100
00:04:06,747 --> 00:04:08,416
IT'S HAPPENING RIGHT NOW.

101
00:04:08,449 --> 00:04:11,485
- WE ARE HERE TODAY TO DETERMINE
WHETHER LESLIE KNOPE

102
00:04:11,519 --> 00:04:13,421
VIOLATED ANY MUNICIPAL RULES
OR LAWS

103
00:04:13,454 --> 00:04:14,988
DUE TO HER ROMANTIC
RELATIONSHIP

104
00:04:15,022 --> 00:04:16,557
WITH HER SUPERIOR BEN WYATT,

105
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:18,392
WHOSE HEARING
WILL BE HELD TOMORROW.

106
00:04:18,426 --> 00:04:20,694
WOULD YOU LIKE TO MAKE
A STATEMENT AT THIS TIME?

107
00:04:20,728 --> 00:04:22,363
- YES.

108
00:04:22,396 --> 00:04:24,432
I FREELY ADMIT
TO THE RELATIONSHIP,

109
00:04:24,465 --> 00:04:25,933
AND I WILL NOT BE FIGHTING
THE CHARGES

110
00:04:25,966 --> 00:04:28,736
THAT WE VIOLATED CHRIS' RULE.

111
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:32,373
BUT WE DID NOTHING ELSE WRONG
OR UNETHICAL.

112
00:04:32,406 --> 00:04:35,643
IN 1849, SARAH NELSON QUINDLE
EXPOSED HER ELBOW OUTDOORS,

113
00:04:35,676 --> 00:04:37,878
WHICH WAS A CLASS "A" FELONY.

114
00:04:37,911 --> 00:04:39,880
ALTHOUGH SHE FELT
THE LAW UNJUST,

115
00:04:39,913 --> 00:04:42,049
SHE ACKNOWLEDGED
THAT SHE HAD BROKEN IT,

116
00:04:42,082 --> 00:04:44,718
AND SHE NOBLY ACCEPTED
HER PUNISHMENT--

117
00:04:44,752 --> 00:04:46,420
TO BE SET ADRIFT
ON LAKE MICHIGAN

118
00:04:46,454 --> 00:04:48,422
LIKE A HUMAN POPSICLE.

119
00:04:48,456 --> 00:04:51,392
LOOK HOW CALM SHE LOOKS.
THAT'S HOW I FEEL--

120
00:04:51,425 --> 00:04:52,726
TOTALLY ZEN.

121
00:04:52,760 --> 00:04:54,462
- MS. KNOPE, ON WHAT DAY

122
00:04:54,495 --> 00:04:57,365
DID YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH BEN WYATT BEGIN?

123
00:04:57,398 --> 00:05:01,702
- LAST MAY, AT YOUR REQUEST,
BEN AND I DROVE TO INDIANAPOLIS

124
00:05:01,735 --> 00:05:03,337
TO BID FOR THE STATE
LITTLE LEAGUE TOURNAMENT.

125
00:05:03,371 --> 00:05:05,773
THE NIGHT WE RETURNED
WAS THE FIRST TIME

126
00:05:05,806 --> 00:05:08,576
WE KISSED EACH OTHER
ON EACH OTHER'S MOUTHS.

127
00:05:08,609 --> 00:05:10,444
IT WAS EXCELLENT.

128
00:05:10,478 --> 00:05:13,481
THAT WAS UNNECESSARY TO ADD.
I'M SORRY. I'M NERVOUS.

129
00:05:13,514 --> 00:05:14,615
[clears throat]
- NEXT QUESTION--

130
00:05:14,648 --> 00:05:17,351
DID YOU EVER RECEIVE
SPECIAL TREATMENT

131
00:05:17,385 --> 00:05:20,087
AS A RESULT OF YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH BEN WYATT?

132
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:23,991
- I RECEIVED ADORABLE NICKNAMES
AND AMAZING BACK RUBS.

133
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:25,593
OH, YOU MEAN PROFESSIONALLY.
NO.

134
00:05:25,626 --> 00:05:28,896
- AND DID YOU BREAK ANY LOCAL,
STATE, OR FEDERAL LAW

135
00:05:28,929 --> 00:05:31,699
IN AN EFFORT TO COVER UP YOUR
RELATIONSHIP WITH BEN WYATT?

136
00:05:31,732 --> 00:05:34,435
- ABSOLUTELY NOT.

137
00:05:34,468 --> 00:05:36,404
- THANK YOU.
MS. KNOPE, THAT IS ALL.

138
00:05:36,437 --> 00:05:38,406
- MR. TRAEGER, THIS SAYS YOU'RE
GONNA BE CALLING 14 WITNESSES.

139
00:05:38,439 --> 00:05:39,807
IS THAT CORRECT?

140
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,008
- UH, YES, SIR.

141
00:05:41,041 --> 00:05:42,009
- 14?
WHY SO MANY?

142
00:05:42,042 --> 00:05:44,545
I'VE ALREADY ADMITTED
THAT I BROKE YOUR RULE.

143
00:05:44,578 --> 00:05:46,814
- IT'S NOT MY RULE, LESLIE.

144
00:05:46,847 --> 00:05:49,683
IT IS AN IMPORTANT RULE
THAT EXISTS IN EVERY GOVERNMENT.

145
00:05:49,717 --> 00:05:51,084
ROMANTIC RELATIONSHIPS

146
00:05:51,118 --> 00:05:53,053
BETWEEN SUPERIORS
AND THEIR EMPLOYEES

147
00:05:53,086 --> 00:05:55,456
LEAD TO FRAUD, CORRUPTION,
AND MISUSE OF PUBLIC FUNDS.

148
00:05:55,489 --> 00:05:56,890
- AND YOU THINK
I'M GUILTY OF THAT?

149
00:05:56,924 --> 00:05:58,492
- I THINK THAT YOU BEGAN
YOUR RELATIONSHIP

150
00:05:58,526 --> 00:06:00,494
WITH BEN WYATT
EARLIER THAN YOU'RE SAYING.

151
00:06:00,528 --> 00:06:02,563
I BELIEVE THAT YOU CERTAINLY
RECEIVED SPECIAL TREATMENT,

152
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:05,132
AND I THINK THAT YOU MAY EVEN
BE GUILTY OF BRIBERY.

153
00:06:05,165 --> 00:06:06,734
- NONE OF THOSE THINGS
ARE TRUE.

154
00:06:06,767 --> 00:06:09,537
AND I WILL PROVE IT,
MR. TRAEGER.

155
00:06:09,570 --> 00:06:11,472
- OKAY, TEN-MINUTE BREAK
PLEASE.

156
00:06:11,505 --> 00:06:12,806
- HERE YOU GO, BOSS.

157
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:15,743
- OKAY, GUYS, WE NEED
TO COUNTER EVERY CHARGE

158
00:06:15,776 --> 00:06:17,578
THAT CHRIS HAS LEVELED
AGAINST ME.

159
00:06:17,611 --> 00:06:19,413
ANDY, I NEED EVIDENCE.
- GOT IT!

160
00:06:19,447 --> 00:06:21,048
- WAIT! YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT EVIDENCE.

161
00:06:21,081 --> 00:06:22,182
- AH, RIGHT ON. YES.
HIT ME.

162
00:06:22,215 --> 00:06:24,184
- NEXT TO MY DESK IS A PICTURE
OF A FEMALE POLITICIAN--

163
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:25,753
BELLA ABZUG.

164
00:06:25,786 --> 00:06:27,688
GET THE KEY THAT'S TAPED
TO THE BACK OF THAT PICTURE.

165
00:06:27,721 --> 00:06:29,022
IT OPENS UP
MY BOTTOM DESK DRAWER

166
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:30,758
IN THERE ARE SOME FILES--
PAY ATTENTION.

167
00:06:30,791 --> 00:06:32,526
WHERE ARE YOU LOOKING?
LOOK HERE, FOCUS HERE.

168
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,794
GET THE FILES IN THE DRAWER,

169
00:06:33,827 --> 00:06:35,162
AND THEN GET ALL THE FILE BOXES
IN THE OFFICE.

170
00:06:35,195 --> 00:06:36,664
- PUT THE FILES IN THE DRAWER.
LET'S GO.

171
00:06:36,697 --> 00:06:38,699
- NO.
- OKAY, I'LL GO WITH HIM.

172
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,200
- THANK YOU.
RON, CHRIS HAS 14 WITNESSES.

173
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,035
I NEED YOU TO TALK
TO ALL THE DEPARTMENT HEADS

174
00:06:42,069 --> 00:06:43,170
AND FIND OUT
WHO'S GONNA TESTIFY.

175
00:06:43,203 --> 00:06:45,539
- I DON'T KNOW THE NAMES
OF THE OTHER DEPARTMENT HEADS.

176
00:06:45,573 --> 00:06:47,641
- I'LL GO WITH HIM. SERIOUSLY?
WITH THE MEN IN THIS OFFICE?

177
00:06:47,675 --> 00:06:48,542
- ANN?
- YEAH?

178
00:06:48,576 --> 00:06:50,444
- I NEED YOU TO TEXT ME
EVERY 30 SECONDS

179
00:06:50,478 --> 00:06:52,079
THAT EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY.

180
00:06:52,112 --> 00:06:53,213
- OKAY.
- [sighs]

181
00:06:53,246 --> 00:06:54,582
[cell phone chimes]

182
00:06:54,615 --> 00:06:57,150
[gasps]
THANKS, ANN!

183
00:06:57,184 --> 00:07:00,053
I BROKE ONE RULE, AND I WILL
ACCEPT A SLAP ON THE WRIST.

184
00:07:00,087 --> 00:07:02,222
BUT WHEN YOU SIT BACK AND LET
YOUR REPUTATION BE DESTROYED.

185
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:07,094
YOU GO DOWN IN HISTORY
AS A FROZEN WHORE.

186
00:07:07,127 --> 00:07:08,496
I'M FIGHTING.

187
00:07:10,864 --> 00:07:12,232
- HEY. GOT MY COMPUTER.
I'M ALL SET.

188
00:07:12,265 --> 00:07:14,167
- GREAT. YOU'RE UP NEXT.
HOW IS BEN? IS HE SAD?

189
00:07:14,201 --> 00:07:15,936
YOU NEED TO CHEER HIM UP, ANN.
- BEN IS FINE.

190
00:07:15,969 --> 00:07:17,671
HE SAYS HE'S SORRY
HE'S NOT IN HERE.

191
00:07:17,705 --> 00:07:19,507
HE SAID TO LOOK
AT THE MONSTER.

192
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:21,174
I'M HOPING YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

193
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:23,511
- THERE'S A RUMOR GOING AROUND
THAT CHRIS HAS A KILLER WITNESS.

194
00:07:23,544 --> 00:07:24,978
- HOW? WHY?
THAT MAKES NO SENSE.

195
00:07:25,012 --> 00:07:26,113
THERE'S NO KILLER WITNESS,

196
00:07:26,146 --> 00:07:27,815
BECAUSE WE DIDN'T DO
ANYTHING WRONG--

197
00:07:27,848 --> 00:07:30,818
UNLESS SOMEONE'S PLANNING
TO LIE OR SLANDER US.

198
00:07:30,851 --> 00:07:33,521
OKAY, JUST TO BE SAFE, FIND OUT
WHO IT IS AND SILENCE HIM.

199
00:07:33,554 --> 00:07:35,889
- WITH PLEASURE.
- WAIT. LET ME MAKE IT CLEAR.

200
00:07:35,923 --> 00:07:40,160
DON'T SILENCE HIM.
JUST MAKE SURE HE CAN'T TALK.

201
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:41,995
- OKAY, WE'RE BACK.

202
00:07:42,029 --> 00:07:43,497
CLEAR THIS CHAMBER, PLEASE.

203
00:07:43,531 --> 00:07:45,766
- MS. PERKINS,
CHRIS TRAEGER HAS QUESTIONED

204
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,568
WHEN MY RELATIONSHIP
WITH BEN WYATT BEGAN.

205
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:49,670
I'D LIKE TO DIRECT YOU
TO YOUR INBOX

206
00:07:49,703 --> 00:07:52,540
AND SPECIFICALLY AN EMAIL
ENTITLED "YAY!"

207
00:07:52,573 --> 00:07:56,644
THAT'S Y-A AND 18 "Y"s
AND 44 EXCLAMATION POINTS.

208
00:07:56,677 --> 00:07:59,647
- YES, IT IS AN EMAIL
FROM YOU.

209
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,081
OH, AND THERE'S AN ATTACHMENT.

210
00:08:01,114 --> 00:08:03,016
- MM.
INTRIGUING.

211
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:05,653
COULD YOU PLAY
THE ATTACHMENT, PLEASE?

212
00:08:05,686 --> 00:08:07,821
- SURE.
[Leslie clears throat]

213
00:08:07,855 --> 00:08:09,990
IN A WORLD ON THE BRINK

214
00:08:10,023 --> 00:08:13,561
OF FINANCIAL MELTDOWN...

215
00:08:13,594 --> 00:08:17,831
IN A TOWN
UNLIKE ANY OTHER...

216
00:08:17,865 --> 00:08:22,202
AN ADORABLE MAN
WITH A CUTE FACE

217
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:26,974
AND THE FUTURE PRESIDENT
OF THE UNITED STATES--

218
00:08:27,007 --> 00:08:28,175
WHAT?--

219
00:08:28,208 --> 00:08:30,744
WENT FROM BEING FRIENDS

220
00:08:30,778 --> 00:08:36,817
TO BEING SO MUCH MORE.

221
