439
00:17:16,603 --> 00:17:18,105
- WHAT?
WAIT. HANG ON.

440
00:17:18,138 --> 00:17:19,739
YOU CAN'T LET HIM RESIGN.

441
00:17:19,772 --> 00:17:21,574
- I TRIED TO TALK HIM
OUT OF IT, BUT...

442
00:17:21,608 --> 00:17:24,711
HIS MIND WAS MADE UP.

443
00:17:24,744 --> 00:17:26,846
LOOK, MY JOB IS TO PROTECT
THE GOVERNMENT

444
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:29,849
FROM FRAUD AND CORRUPTION.

445
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,185
I WAS JUST DOING MY JOB.

446
00:17:32,219 --> 00:17:34,587
I HOPE THAT
YOU CAN UNDERSTAND THAT.

447
00:17:34,621 --> 00:17:36,089
- I DO.

448
00:17:36,123 --> 00:17:37,424
HONESTLY, I DO.

449
00:17:37,457 --> 00:17:39,426
- 'CAUSE YOUR ACTIONS
WOUNDED ME TO MY CORE,

450
00:17:39,459 --> 00:17:41,628
WHICH IS NOT EASY
SINCE THE BULK OF MY WORKOUTS

451
00:17:41,661 --> 00:17:44,564
ARE FOCUSED
ON CORE STRENGTHENING.

452
00:17:44,597 --> 00:17:47,400
BUT WE WILL GET THROUGH THIS.
YOU ARE...

453
00:17:47,434 --> 00:17:49,269
AN EXCELLENT
GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEE.

454
00:17:49,302 --> 00:17:50,870
AND MORE IMPORTANTLY,

455
00:17:50,903 --> 00:17:53,106
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON
I'VE EVER MET WHO'S WORTHY

456
00:17:53,140 --> 00:17:55,575
OF BEING BEN'S GIRLFRIEND.

457
00:17:55,608 --> 00:17:57,310
- I HOPE THAT'S TRUE.

458
00:18:00,313 --> 00:18:02,849
- YOU KNOW, THE MEETING
THAT BEN AND I HAD--

459
00:18:02,882 --> 00:18:04,751
IT'S ON THE RECORD.

460
00:18:04,784 --> 00:18:07,154
YOU SHOULD TAKE A LOOK
AT THE LAST PAGE

461
00:18:07,187 --> 00:18:09,222
OF THE TRANSCRIPT.

462
00:18:11,191 --> 00:18:13,860
- "MR. WYATT:
CHRIS, FOR GOD'S SAKE,

463
00:18:13,893 --> 00:18:16,296
"WOULD YOU MIND NOT JUMPING
FOR A WHILE?

464
00:18:16,329 --> 00:18:18,131
MR. TRAEGER:
SORRY, BEN, BUT"...

465
00:18:18,165 --> 00:18:20,533
- THIS IS HOW
I FIGHT DEPRESSION.

466
00:18:20,567 --> 00:18:21,801
OKAY, FINE.
I'LL STOP.

467
00:18:21,834 --> 00:18:23,436
- THANK YOU.

468
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:26,406
- OKAY, SO YOU ARE PREPARED

469
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:29,209
TO RESIGN,
EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY,

470
00:18:29,242 --> 00:18:32,179
AND TAKE FULL RESPONSIBILITY
FOR ALL THE EVENTS

471
00:18:32,212 --> 00:18:34,681
THAT TRANSPIRED
AT LI'L SEBASTIAN'S MEMORIAL.

472
00:18:34,714 --> 00:18:36,916
- "MR. WYATT: THAT IS CORRECT. "
- THAT IS CORRECT.

473
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:38,585
- "MR. TRAEGER:
OKAY, FINE.

474
00:18:38,618 --> 00:18:40,920
"THIS MAKES ME SADDER
THAN I PREVIOUSLY THOUGHT

475
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:43,856
"HUMANLY POSSIBLE,
BUT I ACCEPT YOUR RESIGNATION.

476
00:18:43,890 --> 00:18:46,359
CAN I ASK YOU
ONE MORE QUESTION?"

477
00:18:46,393 --> 00:18:49,862
- WAS ALL OF THIS--
ALL THE SNEAKING AROUND,

478
00:18:49,896 --> 00:18:51,864
THE SCANDAL,
LOSING YOUR JOB--

479
00:18:51,898 --> 00:18:53,933
WAS IT WORTH IT?

480
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:55,868
- YES.

481
00:18:55,902 --> 00:18:57,637
IT WAS.

482
00:18:57,670 --> 00:18:59,906
- "BECAUSE I LOVE LESLIE.
I WANT TO BE WITH HER.

483
00:18:59,939 --> 00:19:01,408
"AND I DON'T WANT TO HIDE

484
00:19:01,441 --> 00:19:03,810
"THE WAY I FEEL
ABOUT HER ANYMORE.

485
00:19:03,843 --> 00:19:05,345
"SO, YEAH, IT WAS WORTH IT,

486
00:19:05,378 --> 00:19:07,647
"BECAUSE I'M IN LOVE
WITH LESLIE KNOPE.

487
00:19:07,680 --> 00:19:09,816
"MR. TRAEGER:
THAT WAS BEAUTIFUL.

488
00:19:09,849 --> 00:19:12,319
"I'M LITERALLY CRYING
AND JUMPING.

489
00:19:12,352 --> 00:19:15,755
"CRYING NOISE,
CRYING NOISE, NOSE BLOW.

490
00:19:15,788 --> 00:19:17,690
"MR. WYATT:
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

491
00:19:17,724 --> 00:19:18,891
MR. TRAEGER:..."

492
00:19:18,925 --> 00:19:22,161
- [sobbing]
- OH.

493
00:19:23,930 --> 00:19:26,733
LET IT OUT, I GUESS.

494
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:28,335
- "END TRANSCRIPT."

495
00:19:32,405 --> 00:19:34,441
[car door opens, closes]

496
00:19:34,474 --> 00:19:35,875
- HI, HONEY,
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

497
00:19:35,908 --> 00:19:38,878
- OH, I'VE HAD BETTER.

498
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:40,580
HOW ABOUT YOU?

499
00:19:40,613 --> 00:19:42,915
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DID THAT FOR ME.

500
00:19:42,949 --> 00:19:44,517
- WELL, I WAS PRETTY SURE

501
00:19:44,551 --> 00:19:46,819
IT WAS GONNA HAPPEN
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER.

502
00:19:46,853 --> 00:19:48,821
I HOPE IT DOESN'T AFFECT
YOUR CAMPAIGN.

503
00:19:48,855 --> 00:19:50,790
- DON'T WORRY ABOUT THAT
RIGHT NOW.

504
00:19:50,823 --> 00:19:53,793
THERE WAS A PIECE OF TESTIMONY
THAT CAME OUT DURING THE TRIAL

505
00:19:53,826 --> 00:19:57,264
THAT I THINK
YOU'D BE INTERESTED IN.

506
00:19:57,297 --> 00:20:00,500
ETHEL?

507
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:03,570
ETHEL, COULD YOU PLEASE READ
PAGE 132

508
00:20:03,603 --> 00:20:07,607
OF THE OFFICIAL TESTIMONY?

509
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:10,377
- "ETHEL BEAVERS:
THE OFFICIAL RECORD

510
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:13,346
"HAS NOW ANNOYINGLY
BEEN REOPENED

511
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:15,915
"SO THAT LESLIE KNOPE
CAN MAKE A STATEMENT.

512
00:20:15,948 --> 00:20:20,753
"LESLIE KNOPE: LET THE RECORD
STATE THAT I, LESLIE KNOPE,

513
00:20:20,787 --> 00:20:22,389
"LOVE BEN WYATT.

514
00:20:22,422 --> 00:20:24,757
"I LOVE HIM
WITH ALL OF MY HEART.

515
00:20:24,791 --> 00:20:25,992
"DID YOU GET THAT?

516
00:20:26,025 --> 00:20:29,262
ETHEL BEAVERS:
YES, I GOT IT."

517
00:20:29,296 --> 00:20:31,964
- THANK YOU, ETHEL.

518
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,604
- CAN I GET A RIDE HOME?
IT'S FREEZING.

519
00:20:40,673 --> 00:20:43,776
- CAN YOU PLEASE STATE YOUR NAME
FOR THE COMMITTEE?

520
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:46,479
- GARY GERGICH.
- OH, GOD, JERRY.

521
00:20:46,513 --> 00:20:48,315
YOU CAN'T EVEN GET
YOUR OWN NAME RIGHT.

522
00:20:48,348 --> 00:20:50,783
- ACTUALLY,
MY REAL NAME IS GARY.

523
00:20:50,817 --> 00:20:51,718
- GARY?

524
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:53,453
- ON MY FIRST DAY HERE,
THE OLD DIRECTOR--

525
00:20:53,486 --> 00:20:54,687
HE CALLED ME JERRY,

526
00:20:54,721 --> 00:20:56,589
AND I JUST DIDN'T THINK
I SHOULD CORRECT HIM.

527
00:20:56,623 --> 00:20:58,525
- THAT'S RIDICULOUS.
YOUR NAME IS JERRY.

528
00:20:58,558 --> 00:20:59,592
- NO.

529
00:20:59,626 --> 00:21:01,728
LEGALLY MY NAME IS GARY.

530
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:03,730
- GARY GERGICH?

531
00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:05,398
JERRY GERGICH.

532
00:21:05,432 --> 00:21:07,600
GARY GERGICH.
JERRY GERGICH.

533
00:21:07,634 --> 00:21:09,702
GARY GERGICH. JERRY--
GOD, THEY'RE BOTH HORRIBLE.

534
00:21:09,736 --> 00:21:12,772
BUT JERRY'S BETTER.
I'M GONNA CALL YOU JERRY.

535
00:21:12,805 --> 00:21:17,477
OKAY, JERRY, DO YOU REMEMBER
A TIME...

536
00:21:18,778 --> 00:21:20,780
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T GET
OVER THE GARY/JERRY THING.

537
00:21:20,813 --> 00:21:21,914
- NEITHER CAN I.
JERRY, YOU CAN GO.

538
00:21:21,948 --> 00:21:23,450
WE NEED A FIVE-MINUTE BREAK.

